<body>
  
  
  <bookmark branch="index" xml-lang="en-US" id="bm_id3149798"><bookmark_value>charts; bars with texture</bookmark_value><bookmark_value>textures; on chart bars</bookmark_value></bookmark><paragraph id="hd_id3149798" role="heading" level="1" oldref="1" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US"><variable id="chart_barformat"><link href="text/shared/guide/chart_barformat.xhp" name="Adding Texture to Chart Bars">Adding Texture to Chart Bars</link></variable></paragraph>
  <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3156136" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="3">You can add texture to the bars in a graph or chart (instead of the default colors) via bitmap graphics:</paragraph>
  <list type="ordered">
   <listitem>
    <paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3153748" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="4">Enter edit mode by double-clicking on the chart.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3149182" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="5">Double-click on the bar you want to edit. All bars of this series are now selected.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="6" role="listitem" id="par_id3147275" l10n="U">In the context menu choose <emph>Object Properties</emph>. Then choose the <emph>Area</emph> tab.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="7" role="listitem" id="par_id3146797" l10n="U">Click on <emph>Bitmap</emph>. In the list box select a bitmap as a texture for the currently selected bars. Click <emph>OK</emph> to accept the setting.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
  </list>
